                                                                  8234 1451
 The resolved resonance evaluation utilized transmission and      8234 1451
 capture data sets [ref01-02] in the SAMMY code [ref03].          8234 1451
                                                                  8234 1451
 Base resonance parameters taken from JENDL-4 [ref04], adoption   8234 1451
 of these parameters increased the limit of the RRR to 680 keV    8234 1451
 from 475 keV. Due to the prescence of the inelastic channel      8234 1451
 openning below the limit of the RRR, the inelastic cross         8234 1451
 section was calculated in CoH-3 and treated as a background in   8234 1451
 MF-3. Some resonance structure is applied to the inelastic       8234 1451
 channel as a crude approximation. Simply, the energy dependent   8234 1451
 ratio of total-inelastic scattering was calculated. The total    8234 1451
 cross section was then taken from the Horen data sets and used   8234 1451
 to calculate an inelastic cross section that contained the       8234 1451
 resonance structure. This inelastic cross section was subtracted 8234 1451
 from the total cross section and then SAMMY was fit to this      8234 1451
 approximated combination of elastic and capture for neutron and  8234 1451
 radiation widths. This methodology is slightly more realistic    8234 1451
 than using a constant inelastic width in the LRF-7 formalism     8234 1451
 as it accounts for the growing contribution of inelastic         8234 1451
 scattering as a function of energy. However, it is less ideal    8234 1451
 than having an inelastic width per resonance, this latter        8234 1451
 approach is desirable but not obtainable with the  nuclear data  8234 1451
 available.                                                       8234 1451
                                                                  8234 1451
 The effective scattering radius R' was changed to 9.50 fm to     8234 1451
 get proper potential scattering term [ref05].                    8234 1451
                                                                  8234 1451
 Special care was taken for the bound levels of this nucleus to   8234 1451
 provide a positive incoherent scattering length and a capture    8234 1451
 cross section that is consistent with the capture spectra at     8234 1451
 thermal/below the first resonance.                               8234 1451
